AI Usage Documentation
Pretty Cool Resume Builder — CSC3100 Final Project

Summary of AI Usage
This project used Claude (claude.ai) by Anthropic as the primary generative AI assistant during development. The sections below describe how and where AI was used throughout the project.

How AI Was Used
1. New Concepts and Features
Claude assisted with building several UI components and backend features, including the navigation bar and attribution modal. It also helped with specific JavaScript patterns that were new or outside of class material, such as date string formatting, array manipulation, XSS prevention, Toast notifications, and handling user-provided API keys. On the backend, Claude helped align the structure of server.js and app.js with the coding conventions established in prior class projects, and assisted with Gemini API integration and error handling.
2. Debugging and Troubleshooting
Claude was used to help interpret error messages and troubleshoot issues during development, including layout bugs, API response handling, and general runtime errors.
3. In-App AI Features (Gemini)
The application itself uses the Google Gemini API (gemini-2.0-flash) to provide two AI-powered features:

Professional Summary Suggestions — the user writes a draft summary and clicks "AI Suggestion" to receive an improved version from Gemini
Responsibility Bullet Suggestions — the user enters a job responsibility and clicks the magic wand button to receive a more impactful, action-oriented version from Gemini

These features are handled in server.js under the /api/ai/suggest-summary and /api/ai/suggest-responsibility routes.
4. Code Review and Quality Checks
Claude was used to review code for potential issues including XSS vulnerabilities, input validation gaps, and general best practices.

